values.value:
This graph maps the Crowd Control Pluigin's semantic Trigger Names for the available effects in "The Legend of Zelda: A Link To The Past" to more friendly Trigger Names that are easier to remember and work with in your own Node Graphs.

While not strictly necessary for the plugin to function, this serves as a great starting point and provides a solid reference for the effects of this specific game.

For "instant" effects, each "effect-success" trigger is directly mapped to another Tigger with a better name.  "Timed" effects are wired differently: for each of those effects, the corresponding "begin" and "resume" triggers are tied to one Start<effect> trigger, and "end" and "pause" are tied to a similarly-named Stop<effect> trigger.
